Task
The only coins that Alexis has are dimes and quarters.
Her coins have a total value of \$5.80.
She has a total of 40 coins.
Which of the following systems of equations can be used to ﬁnd the number of
dimes, $d$, and the number of quarters, $q$, Alexis has? Explain your choice.
$$
\left\{
\begin{aligned}
d + q &= 5.80 \\
40d + 40q &= 5.80
\end{aligned}
\right.
$$
$$
\left\{
\begin{aligned}
d + q &= 40 \\
0.25d + 0.10q &= 5.80
\end{aligned}
\right.
$$
$$
\left\{
\begin{aligned}
d + q &= 5.80 \\
0.10d + 0.25q &= 40
\end{aligned}
\right.$$
$$
\left\{
\begin{aligned}
d + q &= 40 \\
0.10d + 0.25q &= 5.80
\end{aligned}
\right.
$$
